<div id="review_2416365234" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2416365234" />
    <a title="✨ A ✨ " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/65321843-a"><img alt="✨ A ✨ " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1622901726p2/65321843.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2416365234?book_show_action=true">Jan 19, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="✨ A ✨ " class="user" itemprop="url" name="✨ A ✨ " href="/user/show/65321843-a">✨ A ✨ </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audible Audio " href="/book/show/34211493-the-knife-of-never-letting-go">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/65321843-a?shelf=audiobook">audiobook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/65321843-a?shelf=four-stars">four-stars</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/65321843-a?shelf=young-adult">young-adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/65321843-a?shelf=read-in-2019">read-in-2019</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2416365234" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1306355821204020544"><b>
  <i>The Noise is a man unfiltered, and without a filter, a man is just chaos walking.</i>
</b><br/><br/>This audiobook was very enjoyable. A fast paced read, gripping and intense. Action packed, without a boring chapter. To be completely honest I don&apos;t think I would have liked this book if I&apos;d read a physical copy. The narrator did a really good job.<br/><br/><br/>Todd comes from <i>Prentistown</i>, a men-only town on the planet <i>New World</i>. All the men in <i>Prentistown</i> can hear each others thoughts. They call it the <i>Noise</i>.<br/><br/>But one day Todd</span>
  <span id="freeText1306355821204020544" style="display:none"><b>
  <i>The Noise is a man unfiltered, and without a filter, a man is just chaos walking.</i>
</b><br /><br />This audiobook was very enjoyable. A fast paced read, gripping and intense. Action packed, without a boring chapter. To be completely honest I don't think I would have liked this book if I'd read a physical copy. The narrator did a really good job.<br /><br /><br />Todd comes from <i>Prentistown</i>, a men-only town on the planet <i>New World</i>. All the men in <i>Prentistown</i> can hear each others thoughts. They call it the <i>Noise</i>.<br /><br />But one day Todd is forced to leave his town and on his way he finds a girl, the first female he has ever met. A girl with no <i>Noise</i>.<br /><br />And what's even stranger is that she doesn't even come from his planet!!<br /><br />Both Viola and Todd are on the run searching for a safe place, a place where Viola can contact her ship. <br /><br /><br />On this race to <i>Haven</i> they learn the truth about the beginning of <i>New World</i>. They also learn not to trust anyone but each other.<br /><br /><br />My favourite character was Todd's dog, Manchee. His thoughts made me laugh so much. <br /><br />I didn't expect the protagonist to be so young (13 y/o). It's been a while since I've read about someone younger than 17.<br /><br />I think I would have really liked this book of I'd read it as a teen. Can't wait to see what they do with the movie adaptation.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1306355821204020544" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


